= The Agentic Crew: Crew Member's Guide

_For people who are great with computers — but don't write code._

Rasmus Bornhoft Schlunsen

March 2026

// ─── A Note Before We Start ───

== A Note Before We Start

This book is a companion to _The Agentic Crew: Engineering in the Age of AI Agents_. That book was written for software engineers — people who write code for a living. This one is for everyone else who's good with computers.

Maybe you're a project manager, a designer, a sysadmin, a data analyst, a small business owner, or just the person in your family who fixes the Wi-Fi. You live in spreadsheets, manage inboxes like a general, and right now you have forty-seven browser tabs open. But you've never written a line of code — and you don't need to.

AI agents are changing how software gets built. That affects you, whether you work alongside developers, run a business that depends on software, or just want to understand what's happening in the world around you. The ideas in this book are real. We've simplified the technical details, but we haven't watered them down.

By the time you finish, you'll understand what agents actually are, how modern software works under the hood, and — most importantly — how to direct an agent to build something real. No coding required.

